Even Better Version for Grounded AI
If your AI supports web search but sometimes gives weak trend results, use this stricter version:

Use live web search and only select topics that are trending right now. Do not rely on old internal knowledge if current search results disagree. Prefer topics with visible activity across multiple platforms in the last seven days. If exact trend data is limited, use the strongest available cross-platform signals and clearly state that.

Do not invent trend evidence. If you cannot confirm a trend, exclude it.

When possible, cite or mention the platform evidence behind each trend pick.

