Recommended Final Prompt Template
If you want, this is the version I’d actually use in production:

text

Create a TikTok script about a currently trending animation topic using live web research first.

IMPORTANT:
- Use web search before writing.
- Focus on animation, anime, western animation, or indie animation.
- Prefer trends with strong activity in the last seven days.
- Do not invent trend evidence.
- If trend evidence is unclear, say so.

STEP 1 — Live trend discovery
Search:
- TikTok trending hashtags and edits
- YouTube Shorts / viral clips
- Twitter / X trends
- Google Trends
- recent episode/season releases

Focus on:
- new seasons or episodes
- viral scenes or moments
- characters trending in edits
- meme formats
- repost waves
- fandom spikes

STEP 2 — Generate 5 trend candidates
For each include:
- show name
- why it is trending now
- Trend Score (1–5)
- Content Potential Score (1–5)

If strong on TikTok edits, memes, or YouTube Shorts, add +1 or +2 Trend Score.

Do not penalize a topic just because it has no recent episode if it is still viral.

At least 1 candidate must be:
- western animation
- indie animation
- or meme-driven animation

Remove outdated or weak topics.

STEP 3 — Pick the best trend
Choose the topic with the highest total score.
If tied, prefer:
- strongest social virality
